             <ab>A miracle performed by Our Lady Mary, Holy Twofold Virgin, the Mother of God, may her intercession be with us, amen.
A man in the city of Rome had many sins, and he went every day to the Church of Our Lady Mary Mariham.
When he entered, he always said, “My dear Lady, purify me of the wickedness of my sin! You are the Mother of Mercy, and I know that you will show me mercy. You will not harden your heart against me, dear compassionate one.”1
One day, Our Lady came to him while he was praying this prayer.
She said, “I have forgiven all your previous sins. From now on, don’t return to committing sins.”
Having said this, she disappeared from him, and that man rejoiced joyfully.
May her prayers and her blessings be with us, forever and ever, amen and amen.</ab>
